Meet <b>Sunny</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Sunny lives at <a href='/home/?user=cindi657'>4582 Wild Rose Road</a>, in one of the most beautiful old houses in Ravenwood.  She has been a citizen since August 29, 2004, and has loved every minute here.<br><br>Sunny's classmates at Millsberry Academy describe her as a well-rounded person, both athletic and smart.  Her house holds trophies ranging from Solver to Sink the Three, and her interests include both crossword puzzles and football!<br><br>A very knowledgeable person, Sunny likes to put her sharp mind to work on crossword puzzles of all sizes.  The harder a puzzle is, the more determined she is to finish it!  When Sunny feels like relaxing from all her daily activities, she goes to her room and plays some classic rock, pop, or soft rock on her stereo, and surrounds herself with crossword puzzles.  Her friends say that she's already completed a record number of them!<br><br>If Sunny's not working on one of the numerous puzzles at her desk, then she's usually sitting at her computer, casually typing away.  As lots of her Millsberry Academy classmates can tell you, Sunny has rescued many a book report from vanishing due to her considerable knowledge of computers. <br><br>Sunny also has her athletic side, too.  Weekends will often find her at Peabody Park, playing a casual game of touch football with some friends.  At other times, once the weather gets warmer, she enjoys taking a dip in the pool.  Look for her distinctive pink and violet swimming suit with silver stripes if you feel like joining her for a swim!<br><br>Even if you are not one of her close friends, Sunny always welcomes people who want to hang out with her.  Those who have just met her speak wholeheartedly of Sunny's caring and compassionate nature, and even the shier kids at school are never afraid of approaching her.  Sunny's caring nature carries over to her concern for the community.  She has made a large donation to the Community Center Building Fund, and Sunny regularly participates in efforts to keep Peabody Park clean of trash.<br><br>Thank you for being a fine citizen, Sunny, and congratulations on being chosen as Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
